00:00:57.730 --> 00:01:00.910
If you're hear, you're probably
familiar with 1201, but just,

00:01:00.910 --> 00:01:02.960
I wanted to provide a
little bit of background

00:01:02.960 --> 00:01:05.820
into the statute and
how it was enacted.

00:01:05.820 --> 00:01:09.990
1201 is part of the
DMCA enacted in 1998.

00:01:09.990 --> 00:01:12.460
And in enacting it,
Congress recognized

00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:15.830
that technological protection
measures could be deployed not only

00:01:15.830 --> 00:01:19.370
to prevent piracy and other
economically harmful unauthorized

00:01:19.370 --> 00:01:22.960
uses of copyrighted material,
but also to support new ways

00:01:22.960 --> 00:01:27.980
of dissemination of copyrighted
material to users digitally.

00:01:27.980 --> 00:01:30.350
So Section 1201 protects
circumvention

00:01:30.350 --> 00:01:33.690
of technological measures employed
on or behalf of copyright owners

00:01:33.690 --> 00:01:37.190
to control access to their
works known as access controls,

00:01:37.190 --> 00:01:42.350
as well as anti-trafficking
provisions preventing trade

00:01:42.350 --> 00:01:47.050
in either services or tools of
access controls or copy controls

00:01:47.050 --> 00:01:51.340
that protect rights to
copyright owners under Title 17.

00:01:51.340 --> 00:01:54.700
Section 1201 also includes a
triennial rulemaking process

00:01:54.700 --> 00:01:56.450
by which the Librarian of Congress,

00:01:56.450 --> 00:02:00.550
following a public proceeding
conducted by the Copyright Office,

00:02:00.550 --> 00:02:04.020
in consultation with NTIA,
can grant limited exceptions

00:02:04.020 --> 00:02:08.990
to Section 1201(a)(1)'s bar on the
circumvention of access controls.

00:02:08.990 --> 00:02:12.060
The rulemaking is intended
as a failsafe mechanism

00:02:12.060 --> 00:02:14.480
through which the Copyright
Office can monitor developments

00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:18.020
in the marketplace and recommend
limited exemptions to protect --

00:02:18.020 --> 00:02:22.390
to prevent the restriction of
fair and non-infringing uses.

00:02:22.390 --> 00:02:25.480
The rulemaking has expanded
with each successive cycle.

00:02:25.480 --> 00:02:29.360
In the first rulemaking, the Office
received nearly 400 comments,

00:02:29.360 --> 00:02:32.280
and that resulted in the
granting of two exemptions.

00:02:32.280 --> 00:02:35.540
In the sixth rulemaking, which
was concluded last October,

00:02:35.540 --> 00:02:38.770
we received nearly 40,000 comments.

00:02:38.770 --> 00:02:43.550
We considered 27 categories and
granted 22 of the exemptions.

00:02:43.550 --> 00:02:46.880
Some of the categories in the last
rulemaking concerned the ability

00:02:46.880 --> 00:02:50.180
to access and make
non-infringing uses of works

00:02:50.180 --> 00:02:53.350
such as motion pictures,
ebooks, and videogames.

00:02:53.350 --> 00:02:57.090
But others concerned access
to copyrighted computer code

00:02:57.090 --> 00:03:00.820
in consumer devices ranging
from cell phones to smart TVs,

00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:05.650
automobiles, tractors, 3D
printers and pacemakers.

00:03:05.650 --> 00:03:08.420
The Registrar said
in her recommendation

00:03:08.420 --> 00:03:11.230
that while it's clear 1201
has played an important role

00:03:11.230 --> 00:03:15.060
in developing secure platforms
for digital distribution

00:03:15.060 --> 00:03:18.170
of copyrighted works, it
is also impacting a range

00:03:18.170 --> 00:03:20.110
of consumer activities
that have little to do

00:03:20.110 --> 00:03:22.940
with the consumption
of creative content.

00:03:22.940 --> 00:03:26.170
It also has become obvious that
the regulatory process has become

00:03:26.170 --> 00:03:29.930 position:56%
burdensome for participants in these
rulemakings, especially when seeking

00:03:29.930 --> 00:03:33.590
to renew exemptions and that
the permanent exemptions,

00:03:33.590 --> 00:03:38.700
such as for security research,
encryption research, or privacy,

00:03:38.700 --> 00:03:41.550
may have not adequately
foreseen some

00:03:41.550 --> 00:03:43.890
of the developments since the DMCA.

00:03:43.890 --> 00:03:47.330
