All that's made possible because of
the twin goals achieved by the DMCA.

00:18:00.470 --> 00:18:04.710
When it was passed in 1998, the --

00:18:04.710 --> 00:18:09.160
the thought was, we want
to expand consumer access

00:18:09.160 --> 00:18:13.250
to broadband and to
new technologies.

00:18:13.250 --> 00:18:15.280
And one of the ways
we encourage that is

00:18:15.280 --> 00:18:18.810
by getting copyrighted content
online and on other devices.

00:18:18.810 --> 00:18:21.690
And part of those twin
goals involved 1201.

00:18:21.690 --> 00:18:24.470
We've seen that growth which
makes not only our tradeshow

00:18:24.470 --> 00:18:29.730
but our industry a growing
one, $23.5 billion now, the --

00:18:29.730 --> 00:18:34.990
the largest of the media
companies -industries.

00:18:34.990 --> 00:18:37.970
And that happens because
we know that our investment

00:18:37.970 --> 00:18:40.540
in our technologies
and in our software

00:18:40.540 --> 00:18:44.040
and in our copyrighted
content will get protected.

00:18:44.040 --> 00:18:50.310
When we're talking about
various companies deciding

00:18:50.310 --> 00:18:53.270
to issue certain content
DRM-free, that's a choice.

00:18:53.270 --> 00:18:57.450
1201 doesn't require --
is not a required statute.

00:18:57.450 --> 00:19:00.630
It's -- it's one that says, if
you implement this technology,

00:19:00.630 --> 00:19:05.830
it will have the force of law
if someone tries to bypass it.

00:19:05.830 --> 00:19:07.270
But you don't have to use it.

00:19:07.270 --> 00:19:09.600
And we've seen many models,
even within our own industry,

00:19:09.600 --> 00:19:12.010
with people putting
out games that are free

00:19:12.010 --> 00:19:15.290
to play and freemium models.

00:19:15.290 --> 00:19:17.520
And so, we've seen
the various models win

00:19:17.520 --> 00:19:19.660
out because different games

00:19:19.660 --> 00:19:21.880
and different companies
have different goals.

00:19:21.880 --> 00:19:25.350
It doesn't mean one is mandated and
certainly there's no tech mandate

00:19:25.350 --> 00:19:29.700
in it, but I think, if
companies decide to go DRM-free,

00:19:29.700 --> 00:19:31.460
that's certainly not only allowable

00:19:31.460 --> 00:19:34.220
but that's another way
to access consumers.

