00:39:47.990 --> 00:39:50.630
is a fear that consumers
may have paid for a penny

00:39:50.630 --> 00:39:52.500
but want to access a pound.

00:39:52.500 --> 00:39:55.030
Does your theory take --

00:39:55.030 --> 00:39:58.960
does it matter whether you actually
own the refrigerator or the book

00:39:58.960 --> 00:40:01.880
as opposed to lending, or
leasing, or a subscription model?

00:40:01.880 --> 00:40:04.200
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Band: You
know, I -- I --

00:40:04.200 --> 00:40:09.250
I think there's various
ways to -- to -- to --

00:40:09.250 --> 00:40:12.510
to slice the -- the loaf.

00:40:12.510 --> 00:40:19.350
And certainly, if when we're
amending 1201(a), I mean,

00:40:19.350 --> 00:40:22.690
you could -- I -- I think
the best way to do it is --

00:40:22.690 --> 00:40:26.000
is to simply require a
nexus to infringement

00:40:26.000 --> 00:40:30.030
so if there's really no possibility
of infringement, it's -- it's --

00:40:30.030 --> 00:40:33.830
it's -- it's not within
the scope of the law.

00:40:33.830 --> 00:40:38.050
And -- and it's like when
you're drafting a statute,

00:40:38.050 --> 00:40:40.300
you can either draft it --

00:40:40.300 --> 00:40:44.010
make it really broad and then start
having all kinds of carve-outs

00:40:44.010 --> 00:40:46.790
and you know you're never going to
have enough carve-outs, but it's,

00:40:46.790 --> 00:40:49.340
you know, it's sort of like
who shows up at the table,

00:40:49.340 --> 00:40:53.050
who has enough lobbying strength to
get a carve-out, and that's the --

00:40:53.050 --> 00:40:55.770
unfortunately the approach
taken in 1201.

00:40:55.770 --> 00:40:59.340
The alternative is you have a
narrower bill, more tailored bill,

00:40:59.340 --> 00:41:01.710
and you understand that
there might be some leakage.

00:41:01.710 --> 00:41:05.780
And then, if there's leakage,
then you maybe make amendments

00:41:05.780 --> 00:41:08.460
to take care of --
of -- of those leaks,

00:41:08.460 --> 00:41:11.390
and I think that that's a
better way to approach it.

00:41:11.390 --> 00:41:16.480 position:56%
But, you know, if -- if, you know,
we're not talking about, you know --

00:41:16.480 --> 00:41:18.080
you know, there's other
ways of doing it.

00:41:18.080 --> 00:41:21.330 position:56%
I mean, you could certainly
simply, you know, yeah, you could --

00:41:21.330 --> 00:41:25.890
you could carve out software or --
or software -- embedded software.

00:41:25.890 --> 00:41:28.210
I mean, there's all kinds
of different ways that --

00:41:28.210 --> 00:41:30.340
ways that 1201 could be amended.

00:41:30.340 --> 00:41:34.090
Again, I think a nexus to
infringement would be the best way

00:41:34.090 --> 00:41:39.150
and the simplest way, but there are
certainly other ways that are --

00:41:39.150 --> 00:41:40.670
that -- that would
be less effective,

00:41:40.670 --> 00:41:43.640
but it would be better
than the status quo.

