01:06:12.930 --> 01:06:16.230
a file that was protected
using RealNetworks' DRM,

01:06:16.230 --> 01:06:18.670
you had to authenticate the device
to ensure that you were talking

01:06:18.670 --> 01:06:22.040
to a real server that would protect
against copying of the content.

01:06:22.040 --> 01:06:25.530 position:56%
And somebody had gone in and spoofed
the authentication sequence in order

01:06:25.530 --> 01:06:27.470
to get around that process.

01:06:27.470 --> 01:06:28.860
And so, in order -- they -- they --

01:06:28.860 --> 01:06:30.910
that was really software
that was required to make

01:06:30.910 --> 01:06:32.610
that device work the
way it was supposed to.

01:06:32.610 --> 01:06:35.960
I think in the entertainment field,
