level or a low level,

01:08:42.810 --> 01:08:44.310
it's not for me to judge that.

01:08:44.310 --> 01:08:45.960
What is important is to understand

01:08:45.960 --> 01:08:49.190
that there are rationales behind
each of our uses of software,

01:08:49.190 --> 01:08:50.490
and we've got to be
careful in thinking

01:08:50.490 --> 01:08:52.620
about what we're implicating
and what we're tripping

01:08:52.620 --> 01:08:55.210
over because there would
be unintended consequences.

01:08:55.210 --> 01:08:58.890
And notwithstanding Mr. Band's
idea that we just go really narrow

01:08:58.890 --> 01:09:02.150
and we just fix the "leaks," for
us, the "leaks" are the business.

01:09:02.150 --> 01:09:03.570
You know, once they're
out, they're out.

01:09:03.570 --> 01:09:06.300
And so, it's important for us to
be able to monetize that but also

01:09:06.300 --> 01:09:07.600
to make sure that consumers
are getting it

01:09:07.600 --> 01:09:10.280
in the ways that they want it.

01:09:10.280 --> 01:09:11.580
&gt;&gt; Kevin Amer: Thank you.

01:09:11.580 --> 01:09:12.880
Mr. Zuck?

01:09:12.880 --> 01:09:14.180
&gt;&gt; Jonathan Zuck: Thank you.

01:09:14.180 --> 01:09:16.650
