01:09:45.920 --> 01:09:48.370
so there's some price
discrimination benefits, et cetera,

01:09:48.370 --> 01:09:50.810
to having dynamic business models.

01:09:50.810 --> 01:09:55.020 position:56%
And I think that that's part of what
has made my industry thrive so much.

01:09:55.020 --> 01:09:57.620
I -- I guess I'd rather
approach this from the other end.

01:09:57.620 --> 01:10:02.930 position:56%
If we're trying to -- since we have
the 1201 exemption process in place,

01:10:02.930 --> 01:10:07.530 position:56%
maybe a -- a better reform is trying
to streamline renewals, for example,

01:10:07.530 --> 01:10:09.550
that once you've identified
something

01:10:09.550 --> 01:10:16.900
that is a clearly acceptable use,
you know, make it a lot easier

01:10:16.900 --> 01:10:20.000
to continue that use
somehow, but go --

01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:24.040 position:56%
continue what seems to be a working
process through the Copyright Office

01:10:24.040 --> 01:10:27.010
to determine what are
legitimate uses and -- and just --

01:10:27.010 --> 01:10:30.350
and streamline the process of their
continuation, rather than trying

01:10:30.350 --> 01:10:33.460
to go through and predict
legislatively what --

01:10:33.460 --> 01:10:38.800
into the future, that we don't
even really know what that'll be.

01:10:38.800 --> 01:10:40.840
I mean, like I -- right
now, cameras --

01:10:40.840 --> 01:10:43.170
very often the firmware

01:10:43.170 --> 01:10:46.190
in the camera is what determines
the functionality of the camera.

01:10:46.190 --> 01:10:49.510
So different levels of cameras that
you buy have different firmware

01:10:49.510 --> 01:10:52.210
in them and that's actually what
determines their functionality

01:10:52.210 --> 01:10:56.170
because it creates
manufacturing efficiencies, right.

01:10:56.170 --> 01:10:59.940
So the firmware ends up becoming
really critical to the operation

01:10:59.940 --> 01:11:03.240
of the camera, but it also is
a distinguishing characteristic

01:11:03.240 --> 01:11:05.430
from -- of the camera, as well.

01:11:05.430 --> 01:11:10.030
And I think that that -- we
want to allow that flexibility

01:11:10.030 --> 01:11:11.840
and the efficiencies
that it creates.

01:11:11.840 --> 01:11:15.070
So let's look at this from the
other end and streamline renewals

01:11:15.070 --> 01:11:17.230
