reverse engineering,

01:14:28.710 --> 01:14:33.200
and also every three years, we
revisit many of those issues

01:14:33.200 --> 01:14:36.840
in the context of the -- the
triennial rulemaking proceeding.

01:14:36.840 --> 01:14:39.280
But again, it goes back
to the question of whether

01:14:39.280 --> 01:14:44.050
or not ultimately the issue of
infringement becomes the tail

01:14:44.050 --> 01:14:46.340
that wags the dog of 1201.

01:14:46.340 --> 01:14:51.740
1201 was a recognition that
wholly apart from the issue

01:14:51.740 --> 01:14:56.600
of infringement, there was value
with respect to access to a work

01:14:56.600 --> 01:15:00.300
that had to be within the ability
of the rights holder to control.

01:15:00.300 --> 01:15:03.670
Otherwise, the rights holder
would have little reason to expose

01:15:03.670 --> 01:15:07.870
that work in an online context
for people to be able to access

01:15:07.870 --> 01:15:10.290
and use it without
providing any value

01:15:10.290 --> 01:15:12.320
to the rights holder in return.

01:15:12.320 --> 01:15:14.540
And -- and one thing
that must be kept in mind

01:15:14.540 --> 01:15:16.690
as we discuss these issues is

01:15:16.690 --> 01:15:20.560
that courts have not had any
difficulty whatsoever being able

01:15:20.560 --> 01:15:25.630
to dismiss the notion that fair
use contains a right of access

01:15:25.630 --> 01:15:28.040
to a copy of a copyrighted work.

01:15:28.040 --> 01:15:29.340
It doesn't.

01:15:29.340 --> 01:15:30.640
It never has.

01:15:30.640 --> 01:15:34.940
The arguments in favor of why it
should have never gained any real

01:15:34.940 --> 01:15:38.450
traction, and one can
understand why, because, again,

01:15:38.450 --> 01:15:44.830 position:56%
it would subject the notion of
access as an independent venue of --

01:15:44.830 --> 01:15:49.910
of economic value to be
limited only with respect to how

01:15:49.910 --> 01:15:52.570
that access related to the use.

01:15:52.570 --> 01:15:55.980
And if the use was non-infringing,
whether fair use or not,

01:15:55.980 --> 01:15:58.180
but if it was non-infringing,
you'd be throwing

01:15:58.180 --> 01:16:00.100
out the ability to control access.

01:16:00.100 --> 01:16:04.110
And that's really what
1201 was originally about

01:16:04.110 --> 01:16:06.930
and continues to be about today.

